GOAL:
Write a professional, clear email to the team explaining the Q3 roadmap delay by 3 weeks due to a vendor delay.

CONTEXT:
- Audience: internal team members
- Inputs: Q3 roadmap delay of 3 weeks caused by vendor delay, mitigation plan in progress but not finalized
- Constraints: tone should be professional yet approachable—not too corporate or stiff; avoid blaming the vendor or any team members; clearly communicate what is changing and what remains the same

OUTPUT FORMAT:
- Email subject line
- Email body with:
  - Explanation of the delay without assigning blame
  - Acknowledgment of the mitigation plan in progress
  - Clear summary of changes and what stays the same
  - Professional but conversational tone

QUALITY BAR:
- Include: transparency about the delay, reassurance about mitigation efforts, clarity on roadmap updates
- Avoid: blaming language, overly formal or stiff tone, vague statements
- If uncertain: use neutral, forward-looking language focusing on solutions and next steps

EXAMPLES:
Subject: Update on Q3 Roadmap Timeline  
Body:  
Hi Team,  
I want to update you on a shift in our Q3 roadmap timeline. Due to unforeseen vendor-related delays, our schedule will move back by approximately three weeks. We are actively working on a mitigation plan to address this, and I will share the details as soon as they are finalized. Meanwhile, here’s what is changing and what remains on track...  

SUCCESS CRITERIA:
- Email clearly communicates the 3-week delay without blaming any party  
- Tone balances professionalism with approachability  
- Team understands which roadmap elements are affected and which remain unchanged  
- Mitigation plan status is transparently communicated as in progress  

Verify prompt clarity and completeness before use.